3654/* Allocate and load the module: note that size of section 0 is always
3655 zero, and we rely on this for optional sections. */
3656static int load_module(struct load_info *info, const char __user *uargs,
3657 int flags)
3658{
3659 struct module *mod;
3660 long err;
3661 char *after_dashes;
3662
3663 err = module_sig_check(info, flags);
3664 if (err)
3665 goto free_copy;
3666
3667 err = elf_header_check(info);
3668 if (err)
3669 goto free_copy;
3670
3671 /* Figure out module layout, and allocate all the memory. */
3672 mod = layout_and_allocate(info, flags);
3673 if (IS_ERR(mod)) {
3674 err = PTR_ERR(mod);
3675 goto free_copy;
3676 }
3677
3678 audit_log_kern_module(mod->name);
3679
3680 /* Reserve our place in the list. */
3681 err = add_unformed_module(mod);
3682 if (err)
3683 goto free_module;
3684
3685#ifdef CONFIG_MODULE_SIG
3686 mod->sig_ok = info->sig_ok;
3687 if (!mod->sig_ok) {
3688 pr_notice_once("%s: module verification failed: signature "
3689 "and/or required key missing - tainting "
3690 "kernel\n", mod->name);
3691 add_taint_module(mod, TAINT_UNSIGNED_MODULE, LOCKDEP_STILL_OK);
3692 }
3693#endif
3694
3695 /* To avoid stressing percpu allocator, do this once we're unique. */
3696 err = percpu_modalloc(mod, info);
3697 if (err)
3698 goto unlink_mod;
3699
3700 /* Now module is in final location, initialize linked lists, etc. */
3701 err = module_unload_init(mod);
3702 if (err)
3703 goto unlink_mod;
3704
3705 init_param_lock(mod);
3706
3707 /* Now we've got everything in the final locations, we can
3708 * find optional sections. */
3709 err = find_module_sections(mod, info);
3710 if (err)
3711 goto free_unload;
3712
3713 err = check_module_license_and_versions(mod);
3714 if (err)
3715 goto free_unload;
3716
3717 /* Set up MODINFO_ATTR fields */
3718 setup_modinfo(mod, info);
3719
3720 /* Fix up syms, so that st_value is a pointer to location. */
3721 err = simplify_symbols(mod, info);
3722 if (err < 0)
3723 goto free_modinfo;
3724
3725 err = apply_relocations(mod, info);
3726 if (err < 0)
3727 goto free_modinfo;
3728
3729 err = post_relocation(mod, info);
3730 if (err < 0)
3731 goto free_modinfo;
3732
3733 flush_module_icache(mod);
3734
3735 /* Now copy in args */
3736 mod->args = strndup_user(uargs, ~0UL >> 1);
3737 if (IS_ERR(mod->args)) {
3738 err = PTR_ERR(mod->args);
3739 goto free_arch_cleanup;
3740 }
3741
3742 dynamic_debug_setup(mod, info->debug, info->num_debug);
3743
3744 /* Ftrace init must be called in the MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED state */
3745 ftrace_module_init(mod);
3746
3747 /* Finally it's fully formed, ready to start executing. */
3748 err = complete_formation(mod, info);
3749 if (err)
3750 goto ddebug_cleanup;
3751
3752 err = prepare_coming_module(mod);
3753 if (err)
3754 goto bug_cleanup;
3755
3756 /* Module is ready to execute: parsing args may do that. */
3757 after_dashes = parse_args(mod->name, mod->args, mod->kp, mod->num_kp,
3758 -32768, 32767, mod,
3759 unknown_module_param_cb);
3760 if (IS_ERR(after_dashes)) {
3761 err = PTR_ERR(after_dashes);
3762 goto coming_cleanup;
3763 } else if (after_dashes) {
3764 pr_warn("%s: parameters '%s' after `--' ignored\n",
3765 mod->name, after_dashes);
3766 }
3767
3768 /* Link in to sysfs. */
3769 err = mod_sysfs_setup(mod, info, mod->kp, mod->num_kp);
3770 if (err < 0)
3771 goto coming_cleanup;
3772
3773 if (is_livepatch_module(mod)) {
3774 err = copy_module_elf(mod, info);
3775 if (err < 0)
3776 goto sysfs_cleanup;
3777 }
3778
3779 /* Get rid of temporary copy. */
3780 free_copy(info);
3781
3782 /* Done! */
3783 trace_module_load(mod);
3784
3785 return do_init_module(mod);
3786
3787 sysfs_cleanup:
3788 mod_sysfs_teardown(mod);
3789 coming_cleanup:
3790 mod->state = MODULE_STATE_GOING;
3791 destroy_params(mod->kp, mod->num_kp);
3792 blocking_notifier_call_chain(&module_notify_list,
3793 MODULE_STATE_GOING, mod);
3794 klp_module_going(mod);
3795 bug_cleanup:
3796 /* module_bug_cleanup needs module_mutex protection */
3797 mutex_lock(&module_mutex);
3798 module_bug_cleanup(mod);
3799 mutex_unlock(&module_mutex);
3800
3801 /* we can't deallocate the module until we clear memory protection */
3802 module_disable_ro(mod);
3803 module_disable_nx(mod);
3804
3805 ddebug_cleanup:
3806 ftrace_release_mod(mod);
3807 dynamic_debug_remove(mod, info->debug);
3808 synchronize_sched();
3809 kfree(mod->args);
3810 free_arch_cleanup:
3811 module_arch_cleanup(mod);
3812 free_modinfo:
3813 free_modinfo(mod);
3814 free_unload:
3815 module_unload_free(mod);
3816 unlink_mod:
3817 mutex_lock(&module_mutex);
3818 /* Unlink carefully: kallsyms could be walking list. */
3819 list_del_rcu(&mod->list);
3820 mod_tree_remove(mod);
3821 wake_up_all(&module_wq);
3822 /* Wait for RCU-sched synchronizing before releasing mod->list. */
3823 synchronize_sched();
3824 mutex_unlock(&module_mutex);
3825 free_module:
3826 /* Free lock-classes; relies on the preceding sync_rcu() */
3827 lockdep_free_key_range(mod->core_layout.base, mod->core_layout.size);
3828
3829 module_deallocate(mod, info);
3830 free_copy:
3831 free_copy(info);
3832 return err;
3833}

3835SYSCALL_DEFINE3(init_module, void __user *, umod,
3836 unsigned long, len, const char __user *, uargs)
3837{
3838 int err;
3839 struct load_info info = { };
3840
3841 err = may_init_module();
3842 if (err)
3843 return err;
3844
3845 pr_debug("init_module: umod=%p, len=%lu, uargs=%p\n",
3846 umod, len, uargs);
3847
3848 err = copy_module_from_user(umod, len, &info);
3849 if (err)
3850 return err;
3851
3852 return load_module(&info, uargs, 0);
3853}
3854
3855SYSCALL_DEFINE3(finit_module, int, fd, const char __user *, uargs, int, flags)
3856{
3857 struct load_info info = { };
3858 loff_t size;
3859 void *hdr;
3860 int err;
3861
3862 err = may_init_module();
3863 if (err)
3864 return err;
3865
3866 pr_debug("finit_module: fd=%d, uargs=%p, flags=%i\n", fd, uargs, flags);
3867
3868 if (flags & ~(MODULE_INIT_IGNORE_MODVERSIONS
3869 |MODULE_INIT_IGNORE_VERMAGIC))
3870 return -EINVAL;
3871
3872 err = kernel_read_file_from_fd(fd, &hdr, &size, INT_MAX,
3873 READING_MODULE);
3874 if (err)
3875 return err;
3876 info.hdr = hdr;
3877 info.len = size;
3878
3879 return load_module(&info, uargs, flags);
3880}

3882static inline int within(unsigned long addr, void *start, unsigned long size)
3883{
3884 return ((void *)addr >= start && (void *)addr < start + size);
3885}

3887#ifdef CONFIG_KALLSYMS
3888/*
3889 * This ignores the intensely annoying "mapping symbols" found
3890 * in ARM ELF files: $a, $t and $d.
3891 */
3892static inline int is_arm_mapping_symbol(const char *str)
3893{
3894 if (str[0] == '.' && str[1] == 'L')
3895 return true;
3896 return str[0] == '$' && strchr("axtd", str[1])
3897 && (str[2] == '\0' || str[2] == '.');
3898}

3900static const char *symname(struct mod_kallsyms *kallsyms, unsigned int symnum)
3901{
3902 return kallsyms->strtab + kallsyms->symtab[symnum].st_name;
3903}
3904
3905static const char *get_ksymbol(struct module *mod,
3906 unsigned long addr,
3907 unsigned long *size,
3908 unsigned long *offset)
3909{
3910 unsigned int i, best = 0;
3911 unsigned long nextval;
3912 struct mod_kallsyms *kallsyms = rcu_dereference_sched(mod->kallsyms);
3913
3914 /* At worse, next value is at end of module */
3915 if (within_module_init(addr, mod))
3916 nextval = (unsigned long)mod->init_layout.base+mod->init_layout.text_size;
3917 else
3918 nextval = (unsigned long)mod->core_layout.base+mod->core_layout.text_size;
3919
3920 /* Scan for closest preceding symbol, and next symbol. (ELF
3921 starts real symbols at 1). */
3922 for (i = 1; i < kallsyms->num_symtab; i++) {
3923 if (kallsyms->symtab[i].st_shndx == SHN_UNDEF)
3924 continue;
3925
3926 /* We ignore unnamed symbols: they're uninformative
3927 * and inserted at a whim. */
3928 if (*symname(kallsyms, i) == '\0'
3929 || is_arm_mapping_symbol(symname(kallsyms, i)))
3930 continue;
3931
3932 if (kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value <= addr
3933 && kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value > kallsyms->symtab[best].st_value)
3934 best = i;
3935 if (kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value > addr
3936 && kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value < nextval)
3937 nextval = kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value;
3938 }
3939
3940 if (!best)
3941 return NULL;
3942
3943 if (size)
3944 *size = nextval - kallsyms->symtab[best].st_value;
3945 if (offset)
3946 *offset = addr - kallsyms->symtab[best].st_value;
3947 return symname(kallsyms, best);
3948}

3951 void *ptr)
3952{
3953 return ptr;
3954}

3956/* For kallsyms to ask for address resolution. NULL means not found. Careful
3957 * not to lock to avoid deadlock on oopses, simply disable preemption. */
3958const char *module_address_lookup(unsigned long addr,
3959 unsigned long *size,
3960 unsigned long *offset,
3961 char **modname,
3962 char *namebuf)
3963{
3964 const char *ret = NULL;
3965 struct module *mod;
3966
3967 preempt_disable();
3968 mod = __module_address(addr);
3969 if (mod) {
3970 if (modname)
3971 *modname = mod->name;
3972 ret = get_ksymbol(mod, addr, size, offset);
3973 }
3974 /* Make a copy in here where it's safe */
3975 if (ret) {
3976 strncpy(namebuf, ret, KSYM_NAME_LEN - 1);
3977 ret = namebuf;
3978 }
3979 preempt_enable();
3980
3981 return ret;
3982}

3991 continue;

4005 return -ERANGE;
4006}

4036int module_get_kallsym(unsigned int symnum, unsigned long *value, char *type,
4037 char *name, char *module_name, int *exported)
4038{
4039 struct module *mod;
4040
4041 preempt_disable();
4042 list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod, &modules, list) {
4043 struct mod_kallsyms *kallsyms;
4044
4045 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED)
4046 continue;
4047 kallsyms = rcu_dereference_sched(mod->kallsyms);
4048 if (symnum < kallsyms->num_symtab) {
4049 *value = kallsyms->symtab[symnum].st_value;
4050 *type = kallsyms->symtab[symnum].st_info;
4051 strlcpy(name, symname(kallsyms, symnum), KSYM_NAME_LEN);
4052 strlcpy(module_name, mod->name, MODULE_NAME_LEN);
4053 *exported = is_exported(name, *value, mod);
4054 preempt_enable();
4055 return 0;
4056 }
4057 symnum -= kallsyms->num_symtab;
4058 }
4059 preempt_enable();
4060 return -ERANGE;
4061}

4063static unsigned long mod_find_symname(struct module *mod, const char *name)
4064{
4065 unsigned int i;
4066 struct mod_kallsyms *kallsyms = rcu_dereference_sched(mod->kallsyms);
4067
4068 for (i = 0; i < kallsyms->num_symtab; i++)
4069 if (strcmp(name, symname(kallsyms, i)) == 0 &&
4070 kallsyms->symtab[i].st_info != 'U')
4071 return kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value;
4072 return 0;
4073}
4074
4075/* Look for this name: can be of form module:name. */
4076unsigned long module_kallsyms_lookup_name(const char *name)
4077{
4078 struct module *mod;
4079 char *colon;
4080 unsigned long ret = 0;
4081
4082 /* Don't lock: we're in enough trouble already. */
4083 preempt_disable();
4084 if ((colon = strnchr(name, MODULE_NAME_LEN, ':')) != NULL) {
4085 if ((mod = find_module_all(name, colon - name, false)) != NULL)
4086 ret = mod_find_symname(mod, colon+1);
4087 } else {
4088 list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod, &modules, list) {
4089 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED)
4090 continue;
4091 if ((ret = mod_find_symname(mod, name)) != 0)
4092 break;
4093 }
4094 }
4095 preempt_enable();
4096 return ret;
4097}

4099int module_kallsyms_on_each_symbol(int (*fn)(void *, const char *,
4100 struct module *, unsigned long),
4101 void *data)
4102{
4103 struct module *mod;
4104 unsigned int i;
4105 int ret;
4106
4107 module_assert_mutex();
4108
4109 list_for_each_entry(mod, &modules, list) {
4110 /* We hold module_mutex: no need for rcu_dereference_sched */
4111 struct mod_kallsyms *kallsyms = mod->kallsyms;
4112
4113 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED)
4114 continue;
4115 for (i = 0; i < kallsyms->num_symtab; i++) {
4116 ret = fn(data, symname(kallsyms, i),
4117 mod, kallsyms->symtab[i].st_value);
4118 if (ret != 0)
4119 return ret;
4120 }
4121 }
4122 return 0;
4123}
4124#endif /* CONFIG_KALLSYMS */

4126/* Maximum number of characters written by module_flags() */
4127#define MODULE_FLAGS_BUF_SIZE (TAINT_FLAGS_COUNT + 4)
4128
4129/* Keep in sync with MODULE_FLAGS_BUF_SIZE !!! */
4130static char *module_flags(struct module *mod, char *buf)
4131{
4132 int bx = 0;
4133
4134 BUG_ON(mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED);
4135 if (mod->taints ||
4136 mod->state == MODULE_STATE_GOING ||
4137 mod->state == MODULE_STATE_COMING) {
4138 buf[bx++] = '(';
4139 bx += module_flags_taint(mod, buf + bx);
4140 /* Show a - for module-is-being-unloaded */
4141 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_GOING)
4142 buf[bx++] = '-';
4143 /* Show a + for module-is-being-loaded */
4144 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_COMING)
4145 buf[bx++] = '+';
4146 buf[bx++] = ')';
4147 }
4148 buf[bx] = '\0';
4149
4150 return buf;
4151}

4171static int m_show(struct seq_file *m, void *p)
4172{
4173 struct module *mod = list_entry(p, struct module, list);
4174 char buf[MODULE_FLAGS_BUF_SIZE];
4175 void *value;
4176
4177 /* We always ignore unformed modules. */
4178 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED)
4179 return 0;
4180
4181 seq_printf(m, "%s %u",
4182 mod->name, mod->init_layout.size + mod->core_layout.size);
4183 print_unload_info(m, mod);
4184
4185 /* Informative for users. */
4186 seq_printf(m, " %s",
4187 mod->state == MODULE_STATE_GOING ? "Unloading" :
4188 mod->state == MODULE_STATE_COMING ? "Loading" :
4189 "Live");
4190 /* Used by oprofile and other similar tools. */
4191 value = m->private ? NULL : mod->core_layout.base;
4192 seq_printf(m, " 0x%px", value);
4193
4194 /* Taints info */
4195 if (mod->taints)
4196 seq_printf(m, " %s", module_flags(mod, buf));
4197
4198 seq_puts(m, "\n");
4199 return 0;
4200}

4202/* Format: modulename size refcount deps address
4203
4204 Where refcount is a number or -, and deps is a comma-separated list
4205 of depends or -.
4206*/
4207static const struct seq_operations modules_op = {
4208 .start = m_start,
4209 .next = m_next,
4210 .stop = m_stop,
4211 .show = m_show
4212};
4213
4214/*
4215 * This also sets the "private" pointer to non-NULL if the
4216 * kernel pointers should be hidden (so you can just test
4217 * "m->private" to see if you should keep the values private).
4218 *
4219 * We use the same logic as for /proc/kallsyms.
4220 */
4221static int modules_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *file)
4222{
4223 int err = seq_open(file, &modules_op);
4224
4225 if (!err) {
4226 struct seq_file *m = file->private_data;
4227 m->private = kallsyms_show_value() ? NULL : (void *)8ul;
4228 }
4229
4230 return err;
4231}

4237 .release = seq_release,
4238};

4248/* Given an address, look for it in the module exception tables. */
4249const struct exception_table_entry *search_module_extables(unsigned long addr)
4250{
4251 const struct exception_table_entry *e = NULL;
4252 struct module *mod;
4253
4254 preempt_disable();
4255 mod = __module_address(addr);
4256 if (!mod)
4257 goto out;
4258
4259 if (!mod->num_exentries)
4260 goto out;
4261
4262 e = search_extable(mod->extable,
4263 mod->num_exentries,
4264 addr);
4265out:
4266 preempt_enable();
4267
4268 /*
4269 * Now, if we found one, we are running inside it now, hence
4270 * we cannot unload the module, hence no refcnt needed.
4271 */
4272 return e;
4273}

4275/*
4276 * is_module_address - is this address inside a module?
4277 * @addr: the address to check.
4278 *
4279 * See is_module_text_address() if you simply want to see if the address
4280 * is code (not data).
4281 */
4282bool is_module_address(unsigned long addr)
4283{
4284 bool ret;
4285
4286 preempt_disable();
4287 ret = __module_address(addr) != NULL;
4288 preempt_enable();
4289
4290 return ret;
4291}
4292
4293/*
4294 * __module_address - get the module which contains an address.
4295 * @addr: the address.
4296 *
4297 * Must be called with preempt disabled or module mutex held so that
4298 * module doesn't get freed during this.
4299 */
4300struct module *__module_address(unsigned long addr)
4301{
4302 struct module *mod;
4303
4304 if (addr < module_addr_min || addr > module_addr_max)
4305 return NULL;
4306
4307 module_assert_mutex_or_preempt();
4308
4309 mod = mod_find(addr);
4310 if (mod) {
4311 BUG_ON(!within_module(addr, mod));
4312 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED)
4313 mod = NULL;
4314 }
4315 return mod;
4316}
4317EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(__module_address);
4318
4319/*
4320 * is_module_text_address - is this address inside module code?
4321 * @addr: the address to check.
4322 *
4323 * See is_module_address() if you simply want to see if the address is
4324 * anywhere in a module. See kernel_text_address() for testing if an
4325 * address corresponds to kernel or module code.
4326 */
4327bool is_module_text_address(unsigned long addr)
4328{
4329 bool ret;
4330
4331 preempt_disable();
4332 ret = __module_text_address(addr) != NULL;
4333 preempt_enable();
4334
4335 return ret;
4336}
4337
4338/*
4339 * __module_text_address - get the module whose code contains an address.
4340 * @addr: the address.
4341 *
4342 * Must be called with preempt disabled or module mutex held so that
4343 * module doesn't get freed during this.
4344 */
4345struct module *__module_text_address(unsigned long addr)
4346{
4347 struct module *mod = __module_address(addr);
4348 if (mod) {
4349 /* Make sure it's within the text section. */
4350 if (!within(addr, mod->init_layout.base, mod->init_layout.text_size)
4351 && !within(addr, mod->core_layout.base, mod->core_layout.text_size))
4352 mod = NULL;
4353 }
4354 return mod;
4355}
4356EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(__module_text_address);

4358/* Don't grab lock, we're oopsing. */
4359void print_modules(void)
4360{
4361 struct module *mod;
4362 char buf[MODULE_FLAGS_BUF_SIZE];
4363
4364 printk(KERN_DEFAULT "Modules linked in:");
4365 /* Most callers should already have preempt disabled, but make sure */
4366 preempt_disable();
4367 list_for_each_entry_rcu(mod, &modules, list) {
4368 if (mod->state == MODULE_STATE_UNFORMED)
4369 continue;
4370 pr_cont(" %s%s", mod->name, module_flags(mod, buf));
4371 }
4372 preempt_enable();
4373 if (last_unloaded_module[0])
4374 pr_cont(" [last unloaded: %s]", last_unloaded_module);
4375 pr_cont("\n");
4376}
